Professor Ramamurti
Shankar: Okay.

00:25:56.970 --> 00:26:01.596
His idea was the following.
You take a standard mass and

00:26:01.596 --> 00:26:05.971
you maybe go to a seesaw.
You put the standard mass here

00:26:05.971 --> 00:26:09.571
and you put some other fellow at
the mass you're looking at

00:26:09.571 --> 00:26:11.542
there.
You add just the lengths and

00:26:11.542 --> 00:26:13.912
when it balances,
you can sort of tell what this

00:26:13.912 --> 00:26:17.599
mass is, right?
But suppose you were in outer

00:26:17.599 --> 00:26:20.299
space.
There's no gravity.

00:26:20.299 --> 00:26:23.531
Then the seesaw will balance,
even if you put a potato on one

00:26:23.531 --> 00:26:25.740
side and an elephant on the
